name: No Equipment Workouts
description: Don't have access to any gym equipment? No problem!  This program is perfect for those that have zero equipment but still want some gains!

name: Midseason Maintenance Mode
description: If you are a competitive golfer in the middle of peak season, this is the perfect program to help you play your best while maintaining your gains!

name: Golf Gains For Beginners
description: New to working out?  This 6 week beginner program is a great start for those just starting their golf fitness journey.  Each week will progress you through a variety of workouts geared to jump start your fitness and help you master some of the fundamental movements.

name: Minimal Equipment Workouts
description: If you have a kettlebell, med ball and some bands then hop on board!  This program will give you some elite workouts with just a few pieces of equipment.

name: Hybrid Golfer
description: For golfers that want to add serious strength and build elite endurance.  This program is great for golfers wanting to train for a Hyrox.  The first 6 weeks of this program will have a heavy focus on building a foundation of strength with tempos and isometric movements as well as a base for your running.  The last 6 weeks will focus more on developing your speed along with cardio and muscular endurance.

name: 12 Week Off-season Overhaul
description: Make some serious gains this offseason with this 12 week program.  The first 6 weeks will focus on developing some serious strength and stability which will set the foundation to finish with 6 weeks of developing power and acceleration to get your body primed and ready for next season.

name: Cart Girl Magnet
description: Chicks don't just dig the long ball!  They also like golfers with rock hard abs and bubble butts!  This 8 week body building style program will do just that!

name: Power Bomber Blueprint
description: For those looking to maximize their distance off the tee.  This golf fitness program utilizes lots of heavy lifting and speed work to help you generate maximum power.

name: Look Good Swing Better
description: This is the flagship program designed for golfers wanting to maximize their results on and off the course.  In this program you will get a good balance of mobility work, strength and conditioning, and golf specific accessory work. This program is designed for those that have access to a full gym with all types of equipment.
